That tree's gonna go!

42:40.196 --> 42:42.275
(BOY SCREAMS)

42:43.991 --> 42:46.070
Help me!

42:50.039 --> 42:52.119
Over here!

43:14.898 --> 43:16.764
Help!

43:20.779 --> 43:23.181
Where are the others?

43:23.281 --> 43:25.361
I don't know.

43:26.910 --> 43:28.990
(BOY SCREAMS)

43:34.250 --> 43:36.960
Peter, where are you?

44:17.503 --> 44:19.168
Ralph!

44:20.840 --> 44:23.250
RALPH: (IN DISTANCE) Yeah?

44:40.194 --> 44:42.346
Where are you?

44:42.446 --> 44:44.526
RALPH: Over here.

44:50.495 --> 44:53.482
PIGGY: Wait. Wait for me.

44:53.582 --> 44:55.662
Well, come on.

45:01.132 --> 45:05.169
- Where'd you get that from?
- BOY: Right here.

45:11.893 --> 45:13.962
PIGGY: Ralph!

45:14.062 --> 45:17.186
- Yeah?
- Over here. We found fruit.

45:35.417 --> 45:37.736
Do you think the other guys are okay?

45:37.836 --> 45:42.087
- Who cares?
- Okay, dork. I was just asking.

45:46.011 --> 45:48.803
We should relight the fire.

46:08.826 --> 46:11.938
- Gross.
- BOY: Where are they?

46:12.038 --> 46:15.691
BOY 2: If they didn't get blown away
they're probably hunting.

46:15.791 --> 46:21.322
What good will that do? They can't cook
pigs without a fire. They'll get trichinosis.

46:21.422 --> 46:24.914
- What's that?
- It's bugs that live in pigs.

46:27.053 --> 46:29.133
We knew that.

49:03.254 --> 49:05.334
- (GROANS)
- (SCREAMS)

49:18.478 --> 49:22.633
What's this shit about a monster?
We'll send you back to kindergarten.

49:22.733 --> 49:26.220
- I'm serious.
- Okay, what kind of monster?

49:26.320 --> 49:30.557
Did it have fur and poisoned fangs,
or long, slimy tentacles?

49:30.657 --> 49:34.978
It growled and it came out at me.
And its mouth, it was wet.

49:35.078 --> 49:38.274
- Maybe it was a bear.
- Sounds more like a reptile.

49:38.374 --> 49:41.368
Sounds more like bullshit.

50:01.481 --> 50:03.348
(GROANING)

50:12.826 --> 50:14.693
(GROANING)

50:34.598 --> 50:37.001
- We heard it all right.
- Yeah.

50:37.101 --> 50:40.012
Whatever it is, it's in there.

51:00.958 --> 51:04.528
You should have seen it.
He was scared shitless.

51:04.628 --> 51:09.367
Do you think there was something there?
Some kind of wild animal or something?

51:09.467 --> 51:13.914
- I know it. We heard it growl.
- Is it close?

51:14.014 --> 51:18.042
Just over the big rise
behind our camp. Real close.

51:18.142 --> 51:20.222
Holy shit.

51:23.106 --> 51:26.645
- I just thought you ought to know.
- Yeah.

51:28.153 --> 51:30.862
Thanks for the fire.

51:38.204 --> 51:41.115
ROGER: Here come the reserves.

51:43.043 --> 51:46.155
- Better keep on your toes tonight.
- What do you mean?

51:46.255 --> 51:48.991
- You'll find out.
- What are you doing with that?

51:49.091 --> 51:53.543
Next time we kill a pig,
we're gonna have a barbecue.

51:55.347 --> 52:00.127
- You mean no one's on fire watch?
- Why can't we have the fire down here?

52:00.227 --> 52:03.506
If we want anybody to see the smoke
it's gotta be up there.

52:03.606 --> 52:06.175
Nobody wants to be
up there alone any more.

52:06.275 --> 52:09.678
There's something loose
on this island - a monster.

52:09.778 --> 52:12.689
- There's no monster.
- There's something.

52:13.824 --> 52:17.854
- PIGGY: So what do you want?
- Jack wants the survival knife.

52:17.954 --> 52:20.023
It's not his. It belongs to the camp.

52:20.123 --> 52:23.360
Yeah? Well, there's a new camp now,
and he wants it.

52:23.460 --> 52:26.405
Yeah, and Tony wants his shoes,
socks and his junk.

52:26.505 --> 52:29.157
Take Tony's stuff
but you can't have the knife.

52:29.257 --> 52:34.537
- He's a defector. Another damn defector.
- It's because of the monster.

52:34.637 --> 52:38.125
I told you there's no monster.
Tony knows there's no monster.

52:38.225 --> 52:42.421
Tony just wants to be a hunter
and he's too chickenshit to get his stuff.

52:42.521 --> 52:45.173
But what if there is
some kind of big animal?

52:45.273 --> 52:46.973
Yeah.

53:01.499 --> 53:05.277
PIGGY: Oh, great. Two more traitors.

53:05.377 --> 53:07.696
Sorry, Ralph.

53:07.796 --> 53:10.541
PIGGY: Good riddance.

53:50.799 --> 53:52.464
Sh.

53:53.343 --> 53:55.423
(TWIG SNAPS)

54:07.316 --> 54:09.396
(HUNTERS SHOUT)

54:10.402 --> 54:14.025
JACK:
Go on! Get the knife! Get the knife!

54:20.079 --> 54:22.940
RALPH: Bring that back!
You have no right!

54:23.040 --> 54:27.826
Get back here! What the hell
do you think you're doing?

54:37.305 --> 54:39.957
(PIGGY WHIMPERS)

54:40.057 --> 54:42.460
(SOBS) Oh, God!

54:42.560 --> 54:46.183
They broke my glasses.

55:25.187 --> 55:28.966
Anyone who wants to come up has to ask.

55:29.066 --> 55:31.893
- Where are the others?
- They're hunting.

55:33.112 --> 55:35.987
Where's that cave you found?

55:38.201 --> 55:41.062
- Don't you know?
- Yeah, but I'm not going back.

55:41.162 --> 55:44.565
- I already showed Jack and the others.
- Tell me where it is.

55:44.665 --> 55:46.692
You shouldn't go there.

55:46.792 --> 55:50.533
I just want to look.
I've got a glow stick.

55:52.090 --> 55:55.000
It's over there in the forest.

56:23.789 --> 56:26.498
JACK: Put it here.

56:34.383 --> 56:37.293
Sharpen a stick at both ends.

57:18.803 --> 57:21.714
This is a present for the monster.

58:38.927 --> 58:41.588
(SHOUTING AND WHOOPING)

58:47.769 --> 58:50.923
Okay, Rambo, you've made your point.
What do you want?

58:51.023 --> 58:53.801
We killed a pig today.
There's going to be a feast.

58:53.901 --> 58:56.763
You can all come eat
with us if you want to.

58:56.863 --> 59:02.184
- (WHISPERS) Go on. Now.
- ALL: The chief has spoken.

59:02.284 --> 59:04.364
JACK: See you tonight, girls.

01:00:07.768 --> 01:00:09.878
JACK: Count.
Cadence delay. Cadence count.

01:00:09.978 --> 01:00:13.549
- HUNTERS: Whoa, one.
- JACK: Airborne rangers!

01:00:13.649 --> 01:00:15.217
- Two.
- Better do your best!

01:00:15.317 --> 01:00:16.969
- Three.
- Or you'll find yourself...

01:00:17.069 --> 01:00:18.679
- Four.
- In front leaving rest.

01:00:18.779 --> 01:00:19.514
- One.
- Hit it.

01:00:19.614 --> 01:00:20.348
- Two.
- Hit it.

01:00:20.448 --> 01:00:21.224
- Three.
- Hit it.

01:00:21.324 --> 01:00:22.058
- Four.
- Hit it.

01:00:22.158 --> 01:00:25.270
HUNTERS: One, two, three, four.
One, two, three, four.

01:00:25.370 --> 01:00:27.980
We like it here. We love it here.
We finally found a home.

01:00:28.080 --> 01:00:29.607
- BOY: A what?
- HUNTERS: A home.

01:00:29.707 --> 01:00:33.875
- A what?
- A home away from home. Huh!

01:00:49.185 --> 01:00:51.265
(THUNDERCLAP)

01:01:14.712 --> 01:01:17.587
Luke, take them some meat.

01:01:19.008 --> 01:01:21.493
I promised I'd get meat.

01:01:21.593 --> 01:01:23.673
Didn't I, Ralph?

01:01:24.596 --> 01:01:30.336
I want you to tell the little ones that
I made you a promise and I kept it. Say it!

01:01:30.436 --> 01:01:33.089
You kept your promise
but not the fire watch.

01:01:33.189 --> 01:01:38.385
You think one meal is worth not getting
rescued? We've gotta be one group again.

01:01:38.485 --> 01:01:41.931
I agree. You can join my camp
and have all the meat you want.

01:01:42.031 --> 01:01:44.684
We don't want your meat.

01:01:44.784 --> 01:01:47.437
JACK: Oh, yeah. Then why'd you come?

01:01:47.537 --> 01:01:50.482
RALPH: We came to try
and talk some sense to you.

01:01:50.582 --> 01:01:53.193
You don't have the conch.

01:01:53.293 --> 01:01:56.028
The conch is in our camp,
where it belongs.

01:01:56.128 --> 01:01:59.616
What's the matter, tits?
Were you afraid to bring it with you?

01:01:59.716 --> 01:02:02.410
- The conch doesn't count any more.
- Stop that!

01:02:02.510 --> 01:02:04.871
Nobody's interested in you
and your conch.

01:02:04.971 --> 01:02:11.212
Take your fat friend and shove off.
You've had all the meat you can eat.

01:02:11.312 --> 01:02:13.723
Come on, hunters!

01:02:15.315 --> 01:02:17.395
Roger's the pig!

01:03:16.336 --> 01:03:18.950
(ROGER YELLS)

01:04:24.572 --> 01:04:28.195
Come on, hunters! Billy's the monster!

01:04:54.728 --> 01:04:58.766
The monster!
It's the real monster! Kill him!

01:05:33.977 --> 01:05:36.056
(THUNDERCLAP)

01:05:55.082 --> 01:05:57.993
What are we gonna do?

01:06:00.046 --> 01:06:03.833
Piggy, that was Simon.

01:06:05.968 --> 01:06:10.385
What good are you doing
talking about it? It was dark.

01:06:11.056 --> 01:06:14.210
- We were scared.
- I wasn't scared.

01:06:14.310 --> 01:06:18.218
You were scared.
Anything could have happened.

01:06:21.525 --> 01:06:23.761
It wasn't our fault.

01:06:23.861 --> 01:06:28.391
It was. We were there
and we didn't do anything about it.

01:06:28.491 --> 01:06:32.938
There was nothing we could do.
There was too many of them.

01:06:33.038 --> 01:06:36.483
- That's not the point.
- It was an accident.

01:06:36.583 --> 01:06:40.122
That's what it was...
a terrible accident.

01:06:51.682 --> 01:06:53.761
- Hi.
- Hi.

01:06:56.228 --> 01:06:59.005
We came here to see
if you guys have any fire.

01:06:59.105 --> 01:07:01.185
Ours is out.

01:07:03.318 --> 01:07:07.273
- Everything's out.
- On account of the storm.

01:07:10.284 --> 01:07:13.195
We gotta get back.

01:07:14.663 --> 01:07:17.107
Hold on a minute.

01:07:17.207 --> 01:07:19.902
I wanna talk to you about last night.

01:07:20.002 --> 01:07:21.322
Ralph.

01:07:23.506 --> 01:07:26.075
We left early.

01:07:26.175 --> 01:07:29.086
BOTH: We were real tired.

01:07:44.069 --> 01:07:46.555
- It isn't fair.
- I never touched it.

01:07:46.655 --> 01:07:49.224
- He didn't.
- ROGER: Butt out, or you'll get it.

01:07:49.324 --> 01:07:53.561
From now on, any more criminals
are gonna be put on that island to starve.

01:07:53.661 --> 01:07:57.691
- Give it to him. Whip him.
- Now you're gonna get it.

01:07:58.291 --> 01:07:59.870
(ALL SHOUT) Yeah!

01:08:14.850 --> 01:08:17.428
- (BOY YELLS IN PAIN)
- Stop it!

01:08:22.274 --> 01:08:27.220
I'll get fire, I promise you.
Tomorrow we'll hunt again.

01:08:27.321 --> 01:08:31.058
But we have to be careful
cos the monster might come any time.

01:08:31.158 --> 01:08:33.185
But didn't we... I thought we...

01:08:33.285 --> 01:08:37.189
No. It could come again any time,
in any shape.

01:08:37.290 --> 01:08:40.912
Just when we're not ready,
it could be there.

01:09:05.276 --> 01:09:09.859
PIGGY: Maybe we should
just build a raft and row off.

01:09:11.198 --> 01:09:14.573
RALPH: I will if you will.

01:09:17.122 --> 01:09:21.818
- Well?
- We don't really know what's out there.

01:09:21.917 --> 01:09:25.656
I bet you out past the reef
lots of boats come by every day,

01:09:25.756 --> 01:09:27.908
and one of them could rescue us.

01:09:28.008 --> 01:09:31.953
Yeah? Well, suppose it didn't.
Suppose it was Russian.

01:09:32.054 --> 01:09:34.832
Then what? We'd be taken prisoner.

01:09:34.932 --> 01:09:38.001
The Russians wouldn't take us prisoner.

01:09:38.100 --> 01:09:41.630
I don't know. Major Dingledine,
my new dad, told me...

01:09:41.729 --> 01:09:43.841
Major Dingledine?

01:09:43.941 --> 01:09:47.636
Yeah. He said that if
the Russians invaded the US,

01:09:47.737 --> 01:09:52.688
they would take the kids
and separate us from our parents -

01:09:53.576 --> 01:09:55.853
and I know it sounds weird -

01:09:55.953 --> 01:10:01.664
but they might make us go into
the Olympics or something like that.

01:10:02.543 --> 01:10:05.322
- I don't see what's so funny.
- Piggy,

01:10:05.422 --> 01:10:10.171
I don't think you have to worry about the
Russians forcing you into the Olympics.

01:10:17.600 --> 01:10:20.392
Hey, what's that?

01:10:50.551 --> 01:10:53.260
(SINGS BACH'S MINUET IN G)

01:10:57.600 --> 01:11:00.295
Where do you think it comes from?

01:11:00.395 --> 01:11:05.062
A Russian submarine,
full of Olympic athletes.

01:11:20.082 --> 01:11:22.161
(RUSTLING)

01:11:46.108 --> 01:11:48.817
Ralph, wake up.

01:11:51.238 --> 01:11:54.100
- What is it?
- Sh. Just listen.

01:11:54.200 --> 01:11:57.407
There's someone out there.

01:12:00.622 --> 01:12:03.829
- I don't hear anything.
- Sh. Listen.

01:12:05.169 --> 01:12:07.700
(RUSTLING)

01:12:11.509 --> 01:12:14.496
JACK: I hear you there, Piggy.

01:12:14.596 --> 01:12:18.086
Come outside, Piggy. I want you, Piggy.

01:12:19.141 --> 01:12:21.753
HUNTER: Ha, Piggy!

01:12:21.853 --> 01:12:24.847
Come on out, Piggy.

01:12:27.901 --> 01:12:30.313
(PIGGY WAILS)

01:12:33.782 --> 01:12:37.143
Why can't you just leave us alone?

01:12:37.243 --> 01:12:39.396
- HUNTER: Yagh!
- (PIGGY WAILS)

01:12:39.496 --> 01:12:41.857
- Give 'em back!
- I got the glasses!

01:12:41.957 --> 01:12:44.036
(HUNTERS CHEER)

01:13:02.603 --> 01:13:04.470
(CRYING)

01:13:13.280 --> 01:13:15.147
Here.

01:13:30.881 --> 01:13:35.870
We did everything just the way
grown-ups would have.

01:13:35.970 --> 01:13:38.680
Why didn't it work?

01:13:40.100 --> 01:13:45.171
Things'd be much better, Ralph,
if it wasn't for him.

01:13:45.271 --> 01:13:48.229
I wish he was dead.

01:13:48.900 --> 01:13:52.309
- No, you don't.
- I do.

01:13:56.200 --> 01:14:01.564
We could just give up
and join his tribe.

01:14:01.664 --> 01:14:04.983
Then we'd at least be with the others.

01:14:05.083 --> 01:14:07.531
No, Piggy.

01:14:08.170 --> 01:14:11.994
Ralph, I can't see.

01:14:13.509 --> 01:14:15.921
I know.

01:14:44.707 --> 01:14:47.318
- Halt! Who goes there?
- (WHISTLES)

01:14:47.418 --> 01:14:49.930
RALPH: Don't be stupid.
You know who we are.

01:14:50.030 --> 01:14:52.741
We brought the conch.
I'm calling an assembly.

01:14:52.841 --> 01:14:55.828
- Where's Jack?
- JACK: What do you want now?

01:14:55.928 --> 01:14:59.622
RALPH: You heard. We brought the conch.
I'm calling an assembly.

01:14:59.722 --> 01:15:04.878
Why don't you two fuck off? This is my
end and my tribe. Keep to your own end.

01:15:04.978 --> 01:15:09.341
You won't keep to your end, tearing up
our camp and stealing Piggy's glasses.

01:15:09.441 --> 01:15:12.303
- You've gotta give 'em back.
- Got to? Who says?

01:15:12.403 --> 01:15:14.482
I do.

01:15:15.697 --> 01:15:19.810
Piggy can't see. If you wanted to have
a fire all you had to do was ask.

01:15:19.910 --> 01:15:24.328
- I don't have to ask!
- Come on! Yeah! Yeah!

01:16:01.119 --> 01:16:02.986
(CONCH)

01:16:08.626 --> 01:16:13.365
- PIGGY: I've got the conch. Let me speak.
- Get outta here, Piggy.

01:16:13.465 --> 01:16:15.544
(HUNTERS JEER)

01:16:19.430 --> 01:16:22.066
Stop that, Roger. Let Piggy speak.

01:16:22.266 --> 01:16:24.346
(WOLF-WHISTLES)

01:16:25.143 --> 01:16:28.755
Please. This is serious.

01:16:28.855 --> 01:16:33.059
Get out, fat ass. Get away.
Go back to your own camp.

01:16:34.987 --> 01:16:37.181
What I wanna say is,

01:16:37.281 --> 01:16:42.482
if we don't get rescued
we might have to live here for a long time.

01:16:44.080 --> 01:16:46.473
Maybe the rest of our lives.

01:16:48.375 --> 01:16:54.668
If we are stuck here until we get old
then we can't go on acting like kids.

01:16:56.009 --> 01:16:59.287
We've gotta be sensible
and make things work.

01:16:59.387 --> 01:17:01.086
No!

01:17:31.045 --> 01:17:33.948
You're not gonna get away with this.

01:17:34.048 --> 01:17:38.035
Yeah? And what are you gonna do? Huh?

01:17:38.135 --> 01:17:41.413
What are you gonna do about it?

01:17:41.513 --> 01:17:45.053
You're out of it, pal.
You're on your own.

01:18:23.473 --> 01:18:25.553
(BIRD SQUAWKS)

01:18:38.155 --> 01:18:40.224
About time.

01:18:40.324 --> 01:18:42.852
- You guys by yourselves?
- Yep.

01:18:42.952 --> 01:18:47.647
- Listen, you two, you have to stay awake.
- Give us a break.

01:18:47.747 --> 01:18:51.401
What do you think? You have to be 11
or you can't stand a watch?

01:18:51.501 --> 01:18:53.783
Just stay awake.

01:18:59.385 --> 01:19:03.456
What's the big deal?
There's nobody left except Ralph.

01:19:03.556 --> 01:19:06.709
They're scared of the monster.

01:19:06.809 --> 01:19:11.262
You said we didn't believe
in the monster. You said.

01:19:12.732 --> 01:19:15.607
I'm pretty sure we don't.

01:19:42.720 --> 01:19:44.956
(WHISPERS) Sam! Eric!

01:19:45.056 --> 01:19:47.167
It's me.

01:19:47.267 --> 01:19:49.586
You shouldn't be around here, Ralph.

01:19:49.686 --> 01:19:53.299
You're not allowed. The hunters
are gonna come after you.

01:19:53.399 --> 01:19:59.096
Yeah. And Jack had Roger
sharpen his stick at both ends.

01:19:59.196 --> 01:20:03.642
If that happens, it'll be
because you let it happen.

01:20:03.742 --> 01:20:08.814
If you don't stand up to him
you're just another one of his slaves.

01:20:08.914 --> 01:20:12.288
JACK: Hey, keep alert down there!

01:20:44.326 --> 01:20:48.779
HUNTER: Light another one.
We gotta smoke him out.

01:20:58.882 --> 01:21:01.160
HUNTER: He's over here!

01:21:01.260 --> 01:21:02.924
(YELLS)

01:21:26.494 --> 01:21:28.573
(HUNTER WHISTLES)

01:21:37.463 --> 01:21:39.543
(HUNTER WHISTLES)

01:22:47.201 --> 01:22:49.604
See anything over there?

01:22:49.704 --> 01:22:50.897
No.

01:22:50.997 --> 01:22:53.363
BOTH: Nothing.

01:23:17.399 --> 01:23:19.063
Jack!

01:23:20.110 --> 01:23:22.902
JACK: Get him!

01:24:20.631 --> 01:24:22.498
(SHOUTING)

01:24:43.862 --> 01:24:46.773
What are you guys doing?

